+381|
+382|---
+383|
+384|### 2. Page-Type Catalog
+385|
+386|To enforce structural consistency across contributors, every page in 
NetScript dev documentation must align with its specific catalog type:
+387|
+388|#### A. Multi-Pillar Hub / Front-Door Page
+389|*   *Audience*: Skimmers, Decision Makers, Skeptical Architects.
+390|*   *Tone*: Warm, direct, technically precise (no fluff).
+391|*   *Layout Structure*:
+392|    1.  **Direct Value Title**: Verify the exact problem solved in 2 lines.
+393|    2.  **Interactive Code Tabs**: Side-by-side Contract vs Client 
execution.
+394|    3.  **Comprehensive Card Grid**: Visual representation of the 6 
pillars.
+395|    4.  **Target Personas Breakdown**: Split developer onboarding paths 
cleanly.
+396|    5.  **Exhaustive Comparison Matrices**: Unified table honest about 
weaknesses.
+397|
+398|#### B. Sequential Tutorial Step
+399|*   *Audience*: Devs in training, students.
+400|*   *Tone*: Encouraging, structured, sequential.
+401|*   *Layout Structure*:
+402|    1.  **Progress Indicator / Breadcrumb**: Visual indicator of total 
steps.
+403|    2.  **Objective Section**: "In this step, you will buy..."
+404|    3.  **Prerequisites State Check**: Code state validator command.
+405|    4.  **File-Path Named Code Blocks**: Every block starts with exact 
target file paths.
+406|    5.  **Manual Check Checkbox**: User-interactive step validation.
+407|
+408|#### C. Task-Oriented "How-To" Recipe
+409|*   *Audience*: Working developers solving instant challenges.
+410|*   *Tone*: Direct, concise, practical.
+411|*   *Layout Structure*:
+412|    1.  **Scope Statement**: One sentence explaining what is cooked.
+413|    2.  **Prerequisites Table**: Inputs or active setups needed.
+414|    3.  **Code templates**: Clear highlights of added framework lines.
+415|    4.  **In-Production Pitfalls**: Warning boxes highlighting footguns 
(ports, locks, timeouts).
+416|
+417|#### D. Theoretical "Explanation" Page
+418|*   *Audience*: Senior engineers evaluating internals.
+419|*   *Tone*: Discursive, architectural, analytical.
+420|*   *Layout Structure*:
+421|    1.  **Mental Model / Analogy**: Broad outline of the topic.
+422|    2.  **ASCII Architecture flow-charts**: Layer-by-layer sequence 
mapping.
+423|    3.  **State Transition Tables**: Inputs vs Output states.
+424|    4.  **Design Trade-offs**: Discussion on why this design was chosen and
the alternatives considered.
+425|
+426|---
+427|
+428|### 3. Prioritized Component & Design-System Gap List
+429|
+430|The following elements must be engineered to reach production-grade, 
enterprise documentation standard (ordered by critical need):
+431|
+432|#### Priority 0: Mission-Critical Wayfinding & Usability
+433|-   [ ] **On-Page Scrolling TOC Plugin**: Generates right-hand floating 
list tracking scrolling headers automatically so skimmers navigate massive 
pages.
+434|-   [ ] **In-Header Search box (Pagefind Integration)**: Offline index 
processing, optimizing search result rendering directly inside the sidebar 
layout.
+435|-   [ ] **One-Click Code Copy Hook**: Appends a copy utility to all fenced 
markdown code snippets.
+436|
+437|#### Priority 1: Clear Capability Explanations
+438|-   [ ] **File-Tree Layout Generator (`comp.fileTree`)**: Custom visual 
components rendering directory scaffolds rather than fragile plain text blocks.
+439|-   [ ] **Synchronized System Toggle Tabs (`comp.tabbedRuntime`)**: Injects
identical global localstates so toggling "Deno-KV" or "oRPC Client" rewrites the
active language blocks on all subsequent pages.
+440|-   [ ] **Interactive Badge Indicators (`comp.badge`)**: Adds pills (`OTel 
Wired`, `Contracts First`, `Prisma adapter`) next to headings.
+441|
+442|#### Priority 2: Technical Polish & Refinements
+443|-   [ ] **ASCII Box Layout Canvas**: Structured CSS panels hosting 
monospace flowchart sequences without layout shifts.
+444|-   [ ] **Flex Grid Card Container (`comp.grid`)**: A framework-friendly 
3-col styling layout to host plugin directory listings.
+445|-   [ ] **Persistent Version Switcher (`comp.version`)**: Preserves context
on active packages when jumping between major alpha/beta endpoints.
